</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="240" pageNumber="518" type="breeding">
<paragraph blockId="240.[170,1376,2311,3168]" pageId="240" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,306,2898,2931]" pageId="240" pageNumber="518">Breeding.</emphasis>
Reproductively active Bolson Gerbil Mice are recorded in spring (October— November), with inactive individuals sampled in March and September. Pregnant females have 4-7 embryos.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
